Title: One Hundred Years of Solitude
Author: Gabriel García Márquez
My Review: This book is pure magic. The prose is beautiful, and the story is both sprawling and deeply personal. A haunting, devastating masterpiece that stays with you long after you've finished.

Title: Beloved (Beloved Trilogy, #1)
Author: Toni Morrison
My Review: Painful but necessary reading. Morrison's writing is incredible.

Title: The Buried Giant
Author: Kazuo Ishiguro
My Review: An interesting premise, but the execution felt slow and repetitive. The themes of memory and loss were powerful, but the plot itself didn't grab me.

Title: The Catcher in the Rye
Author: J.D. Salinger
My Review: I just couldn't connect with Holden. He came across as whiny and privileged, not profound. A struggle to get through.
